---
title: Southwest Shrimp & Green Pepper Bowls with Charred Corn Salsa & Cheese
description: Bring bold Southwestern flavors to your table with these chicken and green pepper rice bowls. You’ll serve a spiced mix of sautéed chicken, pepper, and onion over a bed of warm rice, then top it all off with Monterey Jack cheese and a charred corn salsa for a touch of smoky sweetness. All that’s left to do? Finish with a drizzle of tangy crema!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6864b8860203e9f8dbb4c786-5cfe9891.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6864b8860203e9f8dbb4c786-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/southwest-shrimp-and-green-pepper-bowls-6864b8860203e9f8dbb4c786
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 86 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1400 mg
---

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, 1 ¼ cups water (2 ¼ cups for 4 
servings), and a @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to 
low. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to 
serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Drain @corn{1%unit}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Halve, core, and thinly slice 
@long green pepper{1%unit} into strips. Halve, peel, and thinly slice 
@onion{1%unit}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add corn and 
cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and lightly charred in spots, 
~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Cover pan if corn begins to pop!

Turn off heat; transfer corn to a #small bowl{}. Stir in @fresh red salsa{4%ounce} 
and @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}; set aside until ready to serve.

Open package of @shrimp{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for corn over medium-high heat. 
Add shrimp, green pepper, onion, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, 
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, ½ tsp @cumin{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings), 
@salt{} and @pepper{}. (Save remaining cumin for another use.) Cook, stirring 
occasionally, until veggies are just beginning to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Lower heat if chicken and veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Add ¼ cup water and 1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon} (½ cup water and 2 TBSP butter 
for 4). Cook, stirring frequently, until shrimp is cooked through and sauce has 
slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper 
if desired.

Place @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} in a second #small bowl{}. Add water 1 tsp at 
a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{} and top with shrimp and veggies. Top with 
Monterey Jack and corn salsa. Drizzle crema over everything and serve.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.